title: East Bay housing officials fear impact of federal voucher cut
text:
Photo: Lea Suzuki, The Chronicle Annette Miller, rakes leaves in her front yard on Tuesday, October 21, 2015 in Oakland, Calif. Annette Miller, rakes leaves in her front yard on Tuesday, October...
For 10 years, Annette Miller’s federally funded housing voucher for those with low incomes helped anchor her in a modest duplex in West Oakland while many of her neighbors were priced out and had to leave.
